00.0,"total_cash_per_share":0.925,"total_debt":436615008.0,"debt_to_equity":36.002,"current_ratio":4.035,"free_cashflow":-229177744.0,"return_on_equity":0.20087999,"enterprise_value":2310683904.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":9.199,"enterprise_to_revenue":4.118,"earnings_growth":0.323,"shares_outstanding":8659275.0,"float_shares":2405360.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.62969,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-0.91,"fifty_two_week_high":377.0,"fifty_two_week_low":206.0,"fifty_day_average":235.269,"two_hundred_day_avg":260.7085,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":400.0,"all_time_low":200.0,"long_business_summary":"Organic Recycling Systems Limited, an environmental engineering company, provides waste management and valorization solutions in India. The company is involved in the development, construction, and maintenance of waste-to-energy projects in the municipal solid waste (MSW) sector. It also offers engineering, procurement, and construction services; project management consultancy; and commissioning and recommissioning services. In addition, the company provides waste management consulting services for feasibility and DPR preparation, lender/owners engineering, and operational troubleshooting; and laboratory services for feedstock sampling and analysis, compost analysis, and digester analysis. Further, it offers segregation lines for MSW and dry waste segregation; anaerobic digesters and allied equipment; Marut drums for pulverising and recovery; and Sanjeevak carbonisation systems, a biomass-to-charcoal conversion system. The company serves project developers, municipal corporations, corporate institutions, and bulk generators. The company was incorporated in 2008 and is based in Navi Mumbai, India."}}